panels.content:
# Latency Trends

This dashboard breaks down NoisePage's latency by the benchmark type. 
For each benchmark you can compare latency metrics for a specific
number of terminals. You can also compare a latency metric across 
different terminal values. Feel free to mix and match, but be warned
the charts can get overwhelming pretty fast.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  "time" AS "time",
  CASE WHEN 'median' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'median')::numeric END AS "median",
  CASE WHEN 'max' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'max')::numeric END AS "max",
  CASE WHEN 'l_99' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'l_99')::numeric END AS "l_99",
  CASE WHEN 'l_95' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'l_95')::numeric END AS "l_95",
  CASE WHEN 'l_90' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'l_90')::numeric END AS "l_90",
  CASE WHEN 'l_75' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'l_75')::numeric END AS "l_75",
  CASE WHEN 'avg' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'avg')::numeric END AS "avg",
  CASE WHEN 'median' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'median')::numeric END AS "median",
  CASE WHEN 'l_25' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'l_25')::numeric END AS "l_25",
  CASE WHEN 'min' IN ($latency_metrics) THEN (metrics->'latency'->>'min')::numeric END AS "min",
  CONCAT('t = ',(terminals::text),',') AS "terminals"
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("time") AND
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals}) AND
  client_time = 60 AND
  git_branch = 'origin/master' AND
  wal_device = '$wal_device' AND
  max_connection_threads = 32
ORDER BY  time

SELECT
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->'latency'->>$latency_metrics)::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time desc) as "Latest",
    (FIRST_VALUE((metrics->'latency'->$latency_metrics)::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time desc) -
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->'latency'->$latency_metrics)::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time asc)) / 
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->'latency'->$latency_metrics)::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time desc) * 100 as "Change"
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
   $__timeFilter(time) AND 
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals}) AND
  client_time = 60 AND
  git_branch = 'origin/master' AND
  wal_device = '$wal_device' AND
  max_connection_threads = 32
ORDER BY 1
